HEADWORD: Childcrowing
<hw>Child"crow`ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>The crowing noise made by children affected with spasm of the
laryngeal muscles; false croup.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

